A mysterious cipher is being scrawled on the walls around London. 
The first person to see the cipher is dead within hours of reading it. 
Sherlock plunges into a world of codes and symbols, consulting with 
London's best graffiti artists. He soon learns that the city is in the 
grip a gang of international smugglers, a secret society called the Black Lotus.
